quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,85,"When he said to his father and to his people: "
  37,86,""
  37,87,""
  38,64,"Verily, that is the very truth - the mutual dispute of the people of the Fire!"
  38,65,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  38,66,""
  39,49,"When harm touches man, he calls to Us (for help); then when We have (rescued him from that harm and) changed it into a favour from Us, he says: "
  39,50,"Verily, those before them said it, yet (all) that they had earned availed them not."
  39,51,"So, the evil results of that which they earned overtook them. And those who did wrong of these [people to whom you (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) have been sent] will also be overtaken by the evil results (torment) for that which they earned; and they will never be able to escape.{1}",footnotes:1:[{39:51} See the footnote of {5:19}.]
  40,28,"And a believing man of Fir‘aun’s (Pharaoh) family, who hid his faith said: "
  40,29,""
  40,30,"And he who believed said: "
  41,7,"Those who give not the Zakât and they are disbelievers in the Hereafter."
  41,8,"Truly, those who believe (in the Oneness of Allâh, and in His Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم - Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds, for them will be an endless reward that will never stop (i.e. Paradise)."
  41,9,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "